This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it deals with reinforcement learning, a subfield of machine learning. Additionally, the paper explores different reinforcement learning solutions, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. 

The paper also touches on aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as it discusses the ability of machines to navigate complex environments and obtain desired outcomes. 

The use of video game environments suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics), as video games can be used as simulators for testing and training robotic systems. 

The paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), as video games often involve visual input and the use of computer vision techniques may be necessary for the reinforcement learning agents to navigate the environment. 

Finally, the paper may fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics), as video games involve the rendering of graphics and the use of graphics processing units (GPUs) for efficient computation.
